records.addlTxt:
State formally dismisses count 1 on the record, the defendant has provided a valid prescription for suboxone.  Motion granted.  
Count 2 - Possess heroin as repeater - Guilty plea.  Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 3, possess drug paraphernalia.  Motion granted.  Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Maintain full-time employment;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Provide DNA sample;
4) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
5) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
6) One hundred twenty (120) days jail imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion;
7) Pay costs of action;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Minutes.
